<doc>
  <member name="D3D11_DSV_FLAG">
    <summary>
      <para>Depth-stencil view options.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>This enumeration is used by <see cref="D3D11_DEPTH_STENCIL_VIEW_DESC" />.</para>
      <para>Limiting a depth-stencil buffer to read-only access allows more than one depth-stencil view to be bound to the pipeline simultaneously, since it is not possible to have a read/write conflicts between separate views.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d11/d3d11-graphics-reference-resource-enums">Resource Enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D11_DSV_FLAG.D3D11_DSV_READ_ONLY_DEPTH">
    <summary>
      <para>Indicates that depth values are read only.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D11_DSV_FLAG.D3D11_DSV_READ_ONLY_STENCIL">
    <summary>
      <para>Indicates that stencil values are read only.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>